205:      - Auth: local JWT auth replaces Clerk. The Core (per its own `open-source-local-runtime` context) exposes `POST /api/v1/auth/login` + `POST /api/v1/auth/register` + `GET /api/v1/whoami` and issues a short-lived JWT signed with `JWT_SECRET`. The dashboard's `apps/dashboard/src/middleware.ts` replaces `clerkMiddleware()` with a thin `verifyJwtCookie()` helper; the JWT is stored in an `__session` httpOnly cookie. `withAuth` reads the cookie and delegates to the Core's `whoami` to resolve user/tenant/role. `clerkMiddleware()`, the Clerk user-button, the Clerk-hosted sign-in/sign-up UI, and every `@clerk/*` import are removed from the dashboard's runtime. The existing `<SignIn />` / `<SignUp />` mount points become local React forms that POST to a dashboard route handler which calls the Core's `auth/login` and sets the cookie.
