     - On `SIGINT` or `SIGTERM`, the entry point sets `intentionalClose` on the WS client (so the close does not trigger reconnect), closes the WebSocket, awaits `close()` on every driver, and exits 0
     - Any driver `close()` failure is caught and ignored — shutdown is best-effort and never blocks the exit
